Subject: Re: [T2] High crankcase pressure problem after installing new

Sounds like you need to install a nipple in one of the air cleaners to
accept that breather hose. Venting to the outside works if blowby is
low or the nipple on the air cleaner is too restrictive. Otherwise
last hope is a bugpack breather system (drill holes in valve covers
for vent tubes).

John

